<bibRefCitation id="5B2E11D59B30AA2D962EB33BB491051C" author="Grube" box="[530,659,776,801]" firstAuthor="Grube" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref20825" refString="GRUBE A. E. 1878. - Annulata Semperiana. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Annelidenfauna der Philippinen nach den von Herrn Prof. Semper mitgebrachten Sammlungen. Memoires de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences de St. - Petersbourg, 7 me serie 25 (8): 1 - 300, pls 1 - 15. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 46591872" type="journal article" year="1878">Grube, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="77A53FAF9B30AA2D94B8B360B4A50234" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3F006C249B30AA2D94B8B360B4A50234" blockId="8.[131,777,851,1033]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">DIAGNOSIS. — Phyllodocids with prostomium with two globular to conical lateral antennae, median antenna reduced to a nuchal papilla. Four pairs of tentacular cirri, segments 1 and 2 with globose cirri, segment 3 with oblong tapered cirri. Dorsal cirrophore without acicula; supracicular lobes blunt, as long as subacicular ones; ventral cirri oval, blunt. Pharynx with a very long basal region, with tiny globular papillae, distal region minute, smooth surfaces.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="77A53FAF9B30AA2D94B8B406B42D0091" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3F006C249B30AA2D94B8B406B6EA0270" blockId="8.[131,777,1077,1709]" box="[132,232,1077,1103]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F006C249B30AA2D94B8B467B42D0091" blockId="8.[131,777,1077,1709]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
Relevant features that help reinstate 
<taxonomicName id="F8BF17A79B30AA2D9632B467B4890253" authorityName="Bergstrom" authorityYear="1914" box="[526,651,1108,1134]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Sphaerodoce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0DCBB0369B30AA2D9632B467B4890253" box="[526,651,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Sphaerodoce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rely on the anterior part of the body. The 
<typeStatus id="E004D2869B30AA2D95E5B446B40A02B2" box="[473,520,1141,1167]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="F8BF17A79B30AA2D9656B446B7160293" authority="Grube, 1878" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1878" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Phyllodoce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quadraticeps">
<emphasis id="0DCBB0369B30AA2D9656B446B50502B3" box="[618,775,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">P. quadraticeps</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5B2E11D59B30AA2D94B8B4A7B7160293" author="Grube" box="[132,276,1172,1198]" firstAuthor="Grube" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref20825" refString="GRUBE A. E. 1878. - Annulata Semperiana. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Annelidenfauna der Philippinen nach den von Herrn Prof. Semper mitgebrachten Sammlungen. Memoires de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences de St. - Petersbourg, 7 me serie 25 (8): 1 - 300, pls 1 - 15. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 46591872" type="journal article" year="1878">Grube, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the 
<collectingCountry id="47A82CB49B30AA2D9615B4A7B4AA0293" box="[553,680,1172,1198]" name="Philippines" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Philippines</collectingCountry>
; it has a quadratic prostomium, and almost all its tentacular cirri, as well as lateral antennae and palps are all globular, whereas the prostomium is oval to cordate, and cirri are all subulate in 
<emphasis id="0DCBB0369B30AA2D94BAB520B6F80310" box="[134,250,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="F8BF17A79B30AA2D94BAB520B6F40310" box="[134,246,1299,1325]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Phyllodoce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Phyllodoce</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Because these unique features were not included (shape of prostomium, shape of tentacular cirri), the 
<typeStatus id="E004D2869B30AA2D96E4B507B5050373" box="[728,775,1332,1358]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">type</typeStatus>
species groups with other species of 
<emphasis id="0DCBB0369B30AA2D9638B560B4EE0350" box="[516,748,1363,1389]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="F8BF17A79B30AA2D9638B560B4720350" box="[516,624,1363,1389]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Phyllodoce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Phyllodoce</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="16F80D4D9B30AA2D9649B567B4EE0350" box="[629,748,1364,1389]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the phylogeny by 
<bibRefCitation id="5B2E11D59B30AA2D9503B540B7DD03B3" author="Pleijel" box="[319,479,1395,1422]" firstAuthor="Pleijel" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="287 - 299" refId="ref22877" refString="PLEIJEL F. 1993 b. - Phylogeny of Phyllodoce (Polychaeta, Phyllodocidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 108: 287 - 299." type="journal article" year="1993" yearSuffix="b">Pleijel (1993b)</bibRefCitation>
. The papillae pattern on the pharynx was not described by 
<bibRefCitation id="5B2E11D59B30AA2D95F9B5A0B45F0390" author="Grube" box="[453,605,1427,1453]" firstAuthor="Grube" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref20825" refString="GRUBE A. E. 1878. - Annulata Semperiana. Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Annelidenfauna der Philippinen nach den von Herrn Prof. Semper mitgebrachten Sammlungen. Memoires de l'Academie Imperiale des Sciences de St. - Petersbourg, 7 me serie 25 (8): 1 - 300, pls 1 - 15. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 46591872" type="journal article" year="1878">Grube (1878)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="5B2E11D59B30AA2D965BB5A0B6C703F0" author="Gravier" firstAuthor="Gravier" page="1908" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="137 - 282" refId="ref20697" refString="GRAVIER C. 1900. - Contribution a l'etude des annelides polychetes de la Mer Rouge. Nouvelles Archives du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle, 4 me serie 2: 137 - 282. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 36872698" type="journal article" year="1900">Gravier (1900: 1908)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="F8BF17A79B30AA2D950CB587B7CB03F0" authorityName="Grube" authorityYear="1878" box="[304,457,1459,1485]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Phyllodoce" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quadraticeps">
<emphasis id="0DCBB0369B30AA2D950CB587B7CB03F0" box="[304,457,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">P. quadraticeps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the Red Sea and observed the pharynx by dissection, and 
<bibRefCitation id="5B2E11D59B30AA2D95E3B5E0B49103D0" author="Day" box="[479,659,1491,1517]" firstAuthor="Day" page="146" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 458" refId="ref19551" refString="DAY J. H. 1967. - Polychaeta of Southern Africa, Part 1. Errantia. British Museum (Natural History) Publications 656: 1 - 458. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 8725653" type="journal article" year="1967">Day (1967: 146</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 5.2h) illustrated a specimen with a partially exposed pharynx. The pharynx is very long with abundant small papillae, but these Western Indian Ocean records might belong to a different species. 
<bibRefCitation id="5B2E11D59B30AA2D94E2B661B7BE0051" author="Pleijel" box="[222,444,1618,1645]" firstAuthor="Pleijel" page="298" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" pagination="287 - 299" refId="ref22877" refString="PLEIJEL F. 1993 b. - Phylogeny of Phyllodoce (Polychaeta, Phyllodocidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 108: 287 - 299." type="journal article" year="1993" yearSuffix="b">Pleijel (1993b: 298)</bibRefCitation>
listed specimens deposited in several museums and regarded the papillation pattern of the basal pharynx area as dense and diffuse.
</paragraph>
